{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Description","text":"Description"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This environment is the cartpole environment based on the work done by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Barto, Sutton, and Anderson in ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ieeexplore.ieee.org\/document\/6313077"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"just like in the classic environments but now powered by the Mujoco physics simulator -","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allowing for more complex experiments (such as varying the effects of gravity).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This environment involves a cart that can moved linearly, with a pole fixed on it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at one end and having another end free. The cart can be pushed left or right, and the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"goal is to balance the pole on the top of the cart by applying forces on the cart.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Action-Space","text":"Action Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The agent take a 1-element vector for actions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The action space is a continuous ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(action)"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[-3, 3]"},{"text":", where ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"action"},{"text":" represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the numerical force applied to the cart (with magnitude representing the amount of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"force and sign representing the direction)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Max","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Force applied on the cart"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-3"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"3","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Force (N)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Observation-Space","text":"Observation Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The state space consists of positional values of different body parts of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the pendulum system, followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with all the positions ordered before all the velocities.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The observation is a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ndarray","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with shape ","type":"text"},{"code":"(4,)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" where the elements correspond to the following:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Observation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Min"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Max"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"position of the cart along the linear surface"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"position (m)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"vertical angle of the pole on the cart","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"angle (rad)","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"linear velocity of the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slider"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"velocity (m\/s)","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"3","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"angular velocity of the pole on the cart","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"anglular velocity (rad\/s)"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Rewards","text":"Rewards"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The goal is to make the inverted pendulum stand upright (within a certain angle limit)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as long as possible - as such a reward of +1 is awarded for each timestep that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pole is upright."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Starting-State","text":"Starting State"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All observations start in state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0) with a uniform noise in the range"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of [-0.01, 0.01] added to the values for stochasticity."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Episode-End","text":"Episode End"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The episode ends when any of the following happens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Truncation: The episode duration reaches 1000 timesteps.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: Any of the state space values is no longer finite."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: The absolutely value of the vertical angle between the pole and the cart is greater than 0.2 radian."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Arguments","text":"Arguments"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No additional arguments are currently supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["env = gym.make('InvertedPendulum-v4')"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is no v3 for InvertedPendulum, unlike the robot environments where a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"v3 and beyond take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Version-History","text":"Version History"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks (including inverted pendulum)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/init()"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/data","doc:\/\/o